1
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:25,120
Run!

2
00:00:35,350 --> 00:00:36,560
Come on, get down.

3
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,200
What's that?

4
00:00:40,430 --> 00:00:42,030
You all weren't adopted,

5
00:00:42,670 --> 00:00:43,720
that's why you're here.

6
00:00:44,110 --> 00:00:44,950
Move.

7
00:00:45,070 --> 00:00:46,350
It's for a performance.

8
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:47,840
Just got back.

9
00:00:48,670 --> 00:00:50,750
Was it fun?

10
00:00:51,150 --> 00:00:51,990
No.

11
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:54,150
Definitely not.

12
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:11,350
What's wrong, Yimo?

13
00:01:12,430 --> 00:01:14,310
I had another nightmare.

14
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:19,880
Don't be afraid.

15
00:01:20,230 --> 00:01:21,070
Yimo.

16
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:22,680
Dad's here.

17
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:24,070
Go to sleep.

18
00:01:39,420 --> 00:01:43,300
=The Hidden Truth=

19
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,940
=Episode 6=

20
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:47,350
(Goodwood)

21
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:48,280
Sorry

22
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:50,840
about yesterday.

23
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,120
I was drunk
and said the wrong things.

24
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,760
I know in your heart,

25
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,070
Yimo is your real daughter.

26
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:00,790
Honestly,

27
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:03,400
I envy what you two have.

28
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,840
I want her to know

29
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:08,400
she's my real daughter.

30
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:10,150
Not adopted.

31
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:12,710
I just want her

32
00:02:13,630 --> 00:02:15,280
to live a happy life.

33
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,360
Yimo's a good kid.

34
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,870
She'll understand your heart.

35
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:22,840
In my life,

36
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,280
without Yimo,

37
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,400
I'd have sunk long ago.

38
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,800
She's the reason

39
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,430
I climbed out.

40
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:37,750
So I only have one wish

41
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,400
that she's happy

42
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,000
and has a good future.

43
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:51,310
As for me,

44
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,240
I don't matter.

45
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,430
You do matter.

46
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,360
Ali,

47
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,960
you matter a lot

48
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:15,030
to me.

49
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:17,190
I hope my dad can be happy.

50
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,120
You know

51
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,390
it hasn't been easy for him.

52
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:26,430
Everything I do

53
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,510
is for his future.

54
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,720
That's what a daughter should do.

55
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:40,270
About Xiaoqian last time,

56
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,430
I never thanked you.

57
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:45,670
Here's to you.

58
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:07,320
Go easy on the drinks.

59
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:08,790
I'm fine.

60
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,950
Did he give you trouble?

61
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:19,790
No.

62
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:26,510
Did he scold you after?

63
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,630
I get him.

64
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:35,000
No. I don't.

65
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:41,630
Since I came back,

66
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,240
my dad has

67
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:46,070
been acting strange.

68
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,560
Always making excuses to leave,

69
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,270
then disappearing.

70
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:57,310
The restaurant's not that busy, right?

71
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,000
When I got there,

72
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,360
he chased me away.

73
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,390
I asked him,

74
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,870
and he said nothing.

75
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:11,880
Qiang,

76
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,360
do you know what's going on?

77
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:25,640
Yeah.

78
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,270
If I don't know,

79
00:06:28,950 --> 00:06:30,480
how could you?

80
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:37,560
I just hope

81
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,510
it's nothing bad.

82
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,800
If something happens to him,

83
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,360
what would I do?

84
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,240
Don't. You've had too much.

85
00:06:59,510 --> 00:07:00,360
Easy.

86
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,320
I'm fine.

87
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,070
Qiang, I'm fine.

88
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,270
Yimo, you're drunk.

89
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:07,040
Listen to me.

90
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:07,890
Drink no more.

91
00:07:07,890 --> 00:07:08,800
I'm fine.

92
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,640
Really.

93
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,720
Don't drink anymore, Yimo.

94
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:11,870
You've had too much.

95
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:20,110
Qiang.

96
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:24,470
Qiang.

97
00:07:27,430 --> 00:07:28,950
You've been with my dad so long.

98
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:33,360
I'm begging you.

99
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,480
Please watch over him.

100
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,160
Don't let him do anything stupid

101
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:45,800
or dangerous.

102
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,320
Okay?

103
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:56,750
Dirty work's all on us.

104
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:04,680
We don't even know where we're going.

105
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,240
Covered up like this.

106
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,840
What's he pretending for?

107
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,320
I don't know

108
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:33,600
if the pork's gone bad

109
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,200
or the beef's rotten.

110
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,390
These people don't know

111
00:10:39,670 --> 00:10:42,030
how to spend money.

112
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:43,630
Qiang,

113
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,440
ease up.

114
00:10:45,550 --> 00:10:47,120
Let's finish and get out.

115
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,320
Finish what?

116
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,750
Get out?

117
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:54,710
Zhang Ming.

118
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,080
Look at me.

119
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,960
Get out?

120
00:10:57,870 --> 00:10:58,710
Seriously?

121
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,910
Is that gonna cure your mom?

122
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:08,000
Gonna pull us out

123
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,240
of this hellhole?

124
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:11,870
Stop talking.

125
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,240
Hurry up!

126
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:16,680
Qiang,

127
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,960
you're drunk.

128
00:11:20,630 --> 00:11:22,870
Shut up and work.

129
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:35,150
Fine. I'll work.

130
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,320
To hell with this!

131
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,440
Eat?

132
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:48,910
Go eat dirt!

133
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:50,000
What are you doing?

134
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,270
Stay still and don't move.

135
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,480
Leave me alone.

136
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,840
Get him!

137
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:57,710
Qiang!

138
00:12:46,620 --> 00:12:49,580
(Welcome to Hongyun Restaurant)

139
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,840
Ali.

140
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:00,990
What happened?

141
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,600
We didn't even leave yet,

142
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:05,480
and he started drinking,

143
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,390
then caused trouble there.

144
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:10,270
I tried to stop him, but I couldn't.

145
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,790
What did they say?

146
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,390
Didn't give us trouble.

147
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:19,390
Just said you'd know what to do.

148
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:21,000
Take him to the hospital.

149
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:22,120
Don't let this get worse.

150
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,440
Be careful.

151
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:32,630
Okay.

152
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,590
Hello?

153
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:52,960
Master.

154
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:56,390
We can now confirm

155
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,200
(Hongyun Restaurant)
Zhang Ming had direct contact

156
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:00,390
(Related item: sausage)
with the two dog thieves.

157
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,120
We also found food containers

158
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,510
and Hongyun napkins at Liu Yan's.

159
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:05,750
From what we know,

160
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,840
Liu Yan rarely ate out.

161
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,320
I think we should shift focus

162
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,150
(Hongyun Restaurant)
to Zhang Ming and Hongyun Restaurant.

163
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,080
The teahouse is suspicious too.

164
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,600
The dog shelter bought large quantities

165
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:18,350
of the same sausage used in Liu Yan's case.

166
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:20,960
Li Xu is the hidden boss

167
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,670
behind both the shelter and the teahouse.

168
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:25,000
He can't be ruled out.

169
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:30,120
Captain Zhao, we've verified Wang Yimo.

170
00:14:39,270 --> 00:14:40,120
Wang Yimo

171
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:42,440
is Hongyun owner's daughter.

172
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:43,790
She's been to the shelter.

173
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:46,910
She also connects Xiaoqian and the casino.

174
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,120
We can start with her.

175
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:58,870
Master.

176
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,240
She's Huahua.

177
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,630
I don't know the details

178
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:09,550
(Hongyun Restaurant)
of the childhood trauma

179
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:10,440
that cost her memory,

180
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:12,510
but I'm certain

181
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:14,030
she's a victim.

182
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,480
If she were at fault,

183
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,550
why come to me at all?

184
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,200
She'd be trying to avoid me, right?

185
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,390
I told you to keep an eye on her.

186
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,320
Get information if you can.

187
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:30,910
I never said arrest her.

188
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,240
Come on. Keep up.

189
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,480
Be good when you get there.

190
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:38,120
I'll get you some reward.

191
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,000
- Okay.
- Sit in the back.

192
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:41,510
Huahua, get in.

193
00:16:04,390 --> 00:16:06,200
This has always been a knot for me.

194
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:08,080
You know

195
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,320
I feel I owe her.

196
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,840
I don't want to hurt her again.

197
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,240
We've got plenty of ways

198
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,200
to work a case.

199
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,240
You've got tons of tricks.

200
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:19,480
We don't have to use her.

201
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,440
You're crossing a line, kid.

202
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:24,080
This is an investigation,

203
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,670
not a game.

204
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:28,790
If this really ties

205
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,480
to Hongyun,

206
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:31,510
the sooner we know,

207
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:33,720
the safer she is.

208
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,110
Let me ask you.

209
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:45,440
If she's really Huahua,

210
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:47,150
really a Nude Banquet victim,

211
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,720
how did she become Wang Li's daughter?

212
00:16:52,870 --> 00:16:54,240
Have you thought about that?

213
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,440
About the banquet...

214
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,780
(Hongyun Restaurant)

215
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,480
My people trashed your kitchen

216
00:17:16,590 --> 00:17:18,110
and caused you real losses.

217
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,320
I'm sorry.

218
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,160
I'm here to apologize.

219
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:29,390
Mr. Wang,

220
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,310
you didn't handle this right.

221
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,920
Forget the losses.

222
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:37,920
Even meeting like this breaks rules.

223
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,400
Mr. Li,

224
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,040
I've heard

225
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:43,790
that you're a straight shooter.

226
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:44,920
Meeting you today,

227
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,960
the reputation fits.

228
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,270
Looks like we're cut

229
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,400
from the same cloth.

230
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:52,550
So let's be direct.

231
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,840
Mr. Li,

232
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:56,680
don't get played

233
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,790
without knowing it.

234
00:18:06,030 --> 00:18:06,870
Mr. Wang,

235
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:09,550
I don't like beating around the bush.

236
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:10,800
What's more,

237
00:18:11,110 --> 00:18:13,070
I hate being lied to.

238
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:15,030
Say it straight.

239
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,160
Then I will.

240
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:18,630
Bai

241
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:20,880
is a fraud.

242
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:23,270
He hasn't been in Qingcheng long.

243
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,350
No way he had that kind of capital.

244
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,160
No way

245
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,270
he made you that much money.

246
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,030
It all came from me.

247
00:18:32,030 --> 00:18:32,870
You know?

248
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:37,110
One more thing.

249
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:41,110
Do you know he's tied

250
00:18:41,790 --> 00:18:42,630
to a murder?

251
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:46,200
I've been in Qingcheng forever.

252
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:48,920
I know everyone and

253
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:51,270
everything here.

254
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,400
So, Mr. Li,

255
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:56,720
if you want stability, you work with me.

256
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:59,160
Today, we don't talk anything else.

257
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,480
Just your casino.

258
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,640
I know it's currently set up

259
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,110
in an old grain warehouse.

260
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:09,920
I want to move it

261
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,350
from the warehouse

262
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,480
into Hongyun Restaurant.

263
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,280
Look,

264
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,350
big names come here.

265
00:19:19,790 --> 00:19:21,240
We spruce it up.

266
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,510
Great location,

267
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:24,960
lots of traffic.

268
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:27,200
No suspicion.

269
00:19:28,790 --> 00:19:30,440
Why should I trust you?

270
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,960
Your business is solid.

271
00:19:34,110 --> 00:19:34,950
Giving it up?

272
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,750
I'll take ten percent.

273
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,880
We're both victims.

274
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,160
We have to take back

275
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:43,440
what's ours

276
00:19:44,590 --> 00:19:45,430
from Bai.

277
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:50,720
Mr. Wang,

278
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,070
what I hate most

279
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:55,200
is being lied to.

280
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,270
I agree

281
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,000
to your proposal.

282
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,720
I'll move my operation here.

283
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,560
But,

284
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:06,720
one condition.

285
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,310
My business,

286
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:12,200
you stay out of it.

287
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:17,520
Deal.

288
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:30,260
(Hongyun Restaurant)

289
00:20:34,790 --> 00:20:37,510
Old classmate, you've outdone yourself.

290
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,640
If you were done,

291
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,190
you should've said so earlier.

292
00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:42,240
I wouldn't have minded.

293
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,070
Now it's holding things up

294
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,400
and getting messy,

295
00:20:47,790 --> 00:20:49,030
it doesn't look good for you.

296
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,830
It's just a kitchen.

297
00:20:53,970 --> 00:20:55,000
So what if it's wrecked?

298
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:56,430
I can pay.

299
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,080
Old friend,

300
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:03,790
there's new business now.

301
00:21:04,790 --> 00:21:05,830
Why not bring

302
00:21:05,830 --> 00:21:07,880
your old classmate along?

303
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,310
You've built quite a business now.

304
00:21:11,030 --> 00:21:12,720
I did play a small part in it, didn't I?

305
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:18,830
People should know when to be satisfied.

306
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,550
I serve you ten dishes.

307
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:24,000
Can you finish them?

308
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:30,440
When you had the chance before,

309
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,350
you didn't act like this.

310
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:36,190
And

311
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:37,830
how do you know

312
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:39,510
I can't handle it?

313
00:21:49,310 --> 00:21:50,440
I'm already a dead man.

314
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:54,270
What's there to be afraid of?

315
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:10,950
Bai,

316
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:14,590
this isn't the old days.

317
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,110
Your luck

318
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:22,270
won't strike twice.

319
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,520
Dude,

320
00:22:33,110 --> 00:22:34,480
you're too tense.

321
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:38,960
Second chances

322
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,590
aren't up to you.

323
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,240
Relax.

324
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,070
I'm not gonna eat you.

325
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:25,070
After all these years,

326
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,110
you haven't changed much.

327
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:33,800
Mr. Bai,

328
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:36,720
this really was an accident.

329
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,440
Qiang drank too much.

330
00:23:39,070 --> 00:23:40,440
Had nothing to do with me.

331
00:23:40,590 --> 00:23:41,440
Mr. Bai.

332
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:42,350
I know.

333
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:43,400
I get it.

334
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,830
But with all this noise,

335
00:23:46,830 --> 00:23:47,670
it's hard

336
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:50,200
to smooth over.

337
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:52,350
Mr. Bai,

338
00:23:53,830 --> 00:23:55,000
just let me go.

339
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:56,680
I'll do whatever you say.

340
00:23:56,690 --> 00:23:57,550
Really.

341
00:23:57,550 --> 00:23:58,390
I swear.

342
00:23:59,070 --> 00:23:59,910
Mr. Bai.

343
00:23:59,910 --> 00:24:00,830
Zhang Ming,

344
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,510
you saved my life

345
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:09,920
back then.

346
00:24:10,910 --> 00:24:12,360
Why would I make things hard for you?

347
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:15,880
I came back for Wang Li.

348
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,310
This isn't about you.

349
00:24:18,510 --> 00:24:19,480
Go home.

350
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,510
I'll handle this.

351
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,110
If anything comes up,

352
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:26,510
call me.

353
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:28,830
Thanks, Mr. Bai.

354
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:35,280
Zhang Ming.

355
00:24:37,590 --> 00:24:39,310
If I ever need you,

356
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:42,310
be sure to help me.

357
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:47,480
Don't tell anyone

358
00:24:48,550 --> 00:24:49,590
that we met.

359
00:24:53,380 --> 00:24:56,020
(Dalong)

360
00:24:58,750 --> 00:24:59,590
Hello?

361
00:25:00,510 --> 00:25:01,360
No.

362
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:02,320
Don't come over.

363
00:25:03,270 --> 00:25:04,110
Pick a place.

364
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,240
I'll come to you.

365
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:14,590
Bro.

366
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,030
That building deal we talked about?

367
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:18,960
I think it's gonna work.

368
00:25:20,510 --> 00:25:23,240
Which one do we buy first?

369
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:24,960
Good question.

370
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:26,720
Come with me.

371
00:25:28,030 --> 00:25:29,160
Check out how tall it is.

372
00:25:38,830 --> 00:25:39,670
Ming?

373
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:44,160
Enjoy.

374
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,000
Thanks.

375
00:25:55,310 --> 00:25:57,110
Small shops make the best noodles.

376
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:01,400
Why aren't you eating?

377
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:04,920
That's because

378
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,070
you didn't order for him.

379
00:26:08,310 --> 00:26:10,480
Didn't you order for yourself?

380
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:11,830
I'm not hungry.

381
00:26:11,830 --> 00:26:13,550
Now it's awkward.

382
00:26:13,900 --> 00:26:14,750
Order something.

383
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:15,630
Waitress.

384
00:26:15,630 --> 00:26:17,030
- Stop yelling.
- Waitress.

385
00:26:17,070 --> 00:26:17,960
I'm not eating.

386
00:26:19,510 --> 00:26:20,680
Get to the point. What is it?

387
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:25,640
Show it to Ming.

388
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:26,590
Show it.

389
00:26:27,550 --> 00:26:28,390
Come on.

390
00:26:30,310 --> 00:26:31,310
Pig liver noodles, bro.

391
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:32,640
Grab chopsticks, we'll share.

392
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,310
What pig liver noodles?

393
00:26:34,790 --> 00:26:35,960
The business plan.

394
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,790
I told you to keep it in your pocket.

395
00:26:37,790 --> 00:26:38,630
How did you...

396
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:39,680
Got it, bro.

397
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:42,460
(Dalong and Xiaohu's Business Plan)

398
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:45,840
Take a look.

399
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,540
(The Scam-Busters Business Plan)

400
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:52,160
Do you get it or not?

401
00:26:52,350 --> 00:26:53,400
What's this?

402
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,400
Live streams and short videos.

403
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:56,240
I can't do this.

404
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:01,240
You just don't get trends.

405
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:02,790
What's a trend?

406
00:27:03,110 --> 00:27:04,110
A trend means

407
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:06,350
even a pig can fly if it catches the wind.

408
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,640
We're not flying

409
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:09,160
because we don't have you yet.

410
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:10,520
Once you're in,

411
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:12,830
we'll go big together.

412
00:27:13,880 --> 00:27:15,160
I get what you want.

413
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,680
But the restaurant isn't mine.

414
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:18,750
Talking to me won't help.

415
00:27:20,030 --> 00:27:21,750
You may not be the boss,

416
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,720
but you're management.

417
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,310
Say a word to your boss.

418
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:26,510
Wouldn't he give you face?

419
00:27:26,510 --> 00:27:27,960
You wouldn't understand.

420
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:29,960
Our boss is barely

421
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,640
keeping afloat himself.

422
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:33,310
Your boss is drowning?

423
00:27:34,070 --> 00:27:35,590
The restaurant's not so great.

424
00:27:35,830 --> 00:27:37,110
Not as good as the two of us.

425
00:27:37,110 --> 00:27:38,070
Just being honest here.

426
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,000
Just say it. What do you want?

427
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:41,240
Spit it out.

428
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:42,110
With our skills,

429
00:27:42,130 --> 00:27:43,830
we aren't useless to you, right?

430
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:50,520
This thing here

431
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,110
has nothing to do with you two.

432
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:55,190
Stop asking.

433
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:58,400
Guess you still don't know our power.

434
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,480
Listen up.

435
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:04,200
Don't get cocky.

436
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:07,240
That live-stream stuff

437
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:08,680
isn't real business.

438
00:28:08,970 --> 00:28:10,230
The things you had us do before,

439
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:11,350
weren't real work either.

440
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:12,290
Especially the old lady.

441
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:13,400
That really scared us.

442
00:28:17,510 --> 00:28:19,200
Is that something you say out loud?

443
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:23,550
No brain at all.

444
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,680
You act like a total pig.

445
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:27,070
And still think pigs can fly.

446
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:30,590
Relax, Ming.

447
00:28:31,310 --> 00:28:32,400
Let us think it over.

448
00:28:33,510 --> 00:28:34,480
You think it over, too.

449
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,400
After all, this has to be run

450
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:39,240
on a big scale.

451
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,520
It takes some time.

452
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:45,760
Bro, we gotta go now.

453
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:47,510
What's wrong?

454
00:28:47,750 --> 00:28:49,200
I left my wallet at the bathhouse.

455
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,310
My girl's photo's in there.

456
00:28:52,350 --> 00:28:53,510
Let's go. Hurry.

457
00:28:54,590 --> 00:28:55,510
Well,

458
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:58,480
think it over, Ming.

459
00:28:58,510 --> 00:28:59,350
Come on.

460
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:00,590
Later, Ming. Bye.

461
00:29:01,790 --> 00:29:03,200
How did you even forget your wallet?

462
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,960
Sorry, you haven't paid yet.

463
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:18,400
Those two are getting out of control.

464
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:21,400
I need to cut ties.

465
00:29:23,310 --> 00:29:25,400
If things go wrong, we'll get dragged in.

466
00:29:36,110 --> 00:29:36,950
Officer Tang.

467
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:44,590
Master.

468
00:29:47,070 --> 00:29:49,440
From Zhang Ming meeting the brothers...

469
00:29:51,070 --> 00:29:51,910
Easy.

470
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,110
I'm sure

471
00:29:55,030 --> 00:29:57,160
he's the one pulling the strings.

472
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:58,440
That explains

473
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:01,440
how two idiots

474
00:30:01,510 --> 00:30:03,240
pulled off multiple dog thefts.

475
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:05,400
Someone was behind it.

476
00:30:05,830 --> 00:30:07,110
And Zhang Ming called someone

477
00:30:07,310 --> 00:30:09,070
for instructions.

478
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,400
There's someone above him.

479
00:30:13,110 --> 00:30:16,160
He's the accountant at Hongyun.

480
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:18,750
If he's being directed,

481
00:30:18,830 --> 00:30:19,880
his boss Wang Li

482
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:21,310
can't be clean.

483
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:25,160
Out of nowhere,
Wang Li became Huahua's father.

484
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:27,400
What exactly happened?

485
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:29,240
It's pretty suspicious.

486
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:30,950
But Wang Li

487
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,030
isn't the only suspect.

488
00:30:33,510 --> 00:30:35,920
There could be others behind it.

489
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:38,550
Why targeted Liu Yan?

490
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,480
Liu Yan

491
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,270
plus Bai's death...

492
00:30:45,750 --> 00:30:47,270
That leaves either the attackers,

493
00:30:49,350 --> 00:30:50,790
or the victims

494
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,750
whose fate is still unknown.

495
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:56,720
Master.

496
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:00,590
Could the one

497
00:31:01,790 --> 00:31:03,240
behind Zhang Ming...

498
00:31:05,660 --> 00:31:08,580
(A mysterious figure?)

499
00:31:10,110 --> 00:31:12,000
We can't rule either out.

500
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:13,550
But right now,

501
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:16,790
(Hongyun Restaurant)
Wang Li is easier to reach.

502
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:28,110
Got it.

503
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,720
I'll meet Wang Yimo again

504
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,200
and try to get as much as I can

505
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:37,960
without spooking them.

506
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:00,420
Hi, Tang.

507
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,440
Sit. I ordered you a drink.

508
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:03,640
Thanks.

509
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:04,640
You're not busy, right?

510
00:32:04,790 --> 00:32:07,200
Was afraid I'd interrupt work.

511
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,080
Not busy.

512
00:32:08,310 --> 00:32:11,000
I don't really have a job right now.

513
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:13,160
My dad doesn't want me at the restaurant.

514
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,200
I failed

515
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:16,830
helping my friend's shop too.

516
00:32:17,510 --> 00:32:19,440
So I'm basically unemployed.

517
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:20,440
On-call anytime.

518
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:21,920
Don't say that.

519
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:23,920
Why doesn't your dad

520
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,790
let you work at the restaurant?

521
00:32:26,030 --> 00:32:28,240
He thinks I worked too hard for school.

522
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:29,350
Got into a good college.

523
00:32:29,350 --> 00:32:30,920
Shouldn't be carrying plates.

524
00:32:31,550 --> 00:32:33,000
Nothing much, really.

525
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:36,680
He doesn't bring me along

526
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:37,640
when he meets people.

527
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:39,510
He wants me to find a proper job.

528
00:32:39,590 --> 00:32:41,070
Says he's worried I'd be tired.

529
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:43,110
But working is tiring too.

530
00:32:44,110 --> 00:32:45,030
He doesn't get that.

531
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:47,000
He means well.

532
00:32:52,550 --> 00:32:55,070
Has he met anyone unusual lately?

533
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:57,310
Anything different you've noticed?

534
00:32:58,880 --> 00:32:59,720
Tang,

535
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,270
did something happen?

536
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:03,590
Is this about my dad?

537
00:33:04,750 --> 00:33:06,310
He didn't do anything.

538
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,000
I...

539
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:12,070
This is just cop instinct.

540
00:33:13,730 --> 00:33:14,580
It's fine.

541
00:33:14,590 --> 00:33:16,440
Anyway, I know my dad's clean.

542
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:17,440
I trust him.

543
00:33:19,310 --> 00:33:21,590
The only odd thing.

544
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,960
He promised

545
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,400
to go to Xinjing with me,

546
00:33:25,550 --> 00:33:28,030
then suddenly said he couldn't.

547
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:30,030
As for why,

548
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:31,880
I'm in the dark.

549
00:33:34,310 --> 00:33:36,880
I did see a man at the restaurant.

550
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:39,680
Something felt off.

551
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,270
He even said hi.

552
00:33:41,510 --> 00:33:43,720
Never saw him again.

553
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,350
What did he look like?

554
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:48,190
Can you describe him?

555
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:52,400
Pretty ordinary.

556
00:33:52,790 --> 00:33:55,920
Just felt wrong.

557
00:33:58,350 --> 00:34:00,550
How did the staff react to him?

558
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,550
Not sure.

559
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,750
He was leaving when I arrived.

560
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:09,390
I see.

561
00:34:12,070 --> 00:34:12,960
You just graduated.

562
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:14,230
Haven't seen much yet.

563
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,230
Actually, public safety's good

564
00:34:17,230 --> 00:34:18,280
these days.

565
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,280
Quite safe overall.

566
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:22,320
But still, stay alert.

567
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:23,670
Keep yourself safe.

568
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:27,280
That's why I call you
whenever something happens.

569
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:28,280
Sorry about that.

570
00:34:28,590 --> 00:34:30,000
You did the right thing.

571
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:37,760
Yimo,

572
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,440
do you still remember

573
00:34:40,550 --> 00:34:42,360
how your were adopted?

574
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:49,150
Not really.

575
00:34:50,110 --> 00:34:51,920
I always thought I was his real child.

576
00:34:52,550 --> 00:34:55,960
I heard

577
00:34:56,070 --> 00:34:57,960
I was adopted,

578
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:00,840
but my dad said it wasn't true.

579
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:03,590
Besides, my dad really loved me.

580
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,000
Growing up,

581
00:35:05,710 --> 00:35:07,590
nothing mattered more than me.

582
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:14,550
Try to think harder.

583
00:35:16,110 --> 00:35:18,150
What happened before you lost your memory?

584
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,190
Even tiny fragments would help.

585
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:31,510
Like the welfare home.

586
00:35:35,030 --> 00:35:35,870
The kitchen.

587
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:37,550
Next.

588
00:35:38,070 --> 00:35:38,920
The table.

589
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:40,230
You're so skinny.

590
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:53,710
I need some air.

591
00:36:29,670 --> 00:36:30,670
Sorry, Yimo.

592
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,510
That was out of line.

593
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,320
I didn't mean to bring this up.

594
00:36:39,150 --> 00:36:40,280
What happened to Huahua

595
00:36:41,550 --> 00:36:42,590
has been stuck

596
00:36:48,510 --> 00:36:49,670
in my throat for years.

597
00:36:51,590 --> 00:36:52,920
I keep thinking

598
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:54,230
if I'd been braver as a kid,

599
00:36:55,070 --> 00:36:57,800
maybe things would be different now.

600
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:01,600
Tang,

601
00:37:05,590 --> 00:37:07,400
did something happen to my dad?

602
00:37:13,230 --> 00:37:14,630
He's a good man.

603
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:17,710
He's never done anything bad.

604
00:37:20,110 --> 00:37:21,230
He loves me.

605
00:37:22,510 --> 00:37:23,840
I can't lose him.

606
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,110
If you're checking him,

607
00:37:26,210 --> 00:37:27,630
please make sure you get it right.

608
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:32,120
I can't even imagine

609
00:37:32,130 --> 00:37:33,800
him doing something wrong.

610
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:43,550
Don't be afraid.

611
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,640
Right now

612
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:50,360
it's just Zhang Ming

613
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:53,070
might be tied to the case.

614
00:37:54,710 --> 00:37:56,320
That's all I can say.

615
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:58,320
If your dad were really a problem,

616
00:37:58,980 --> 00:38:00,590
I wouldn't have brought you here today.

617
00:38:01,030 --> 00:38:01,870
Right?

618
00:38:02,710 --> 00:38:03,550
Really?

619
00:38:04,150 --> 00:38:04,990
Trust me.

620
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:11,240
Get back.

621
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,800
There's a market over there.

622
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:16,800
Wanna take a look?

623
00:38:18,800 --> 00:38:19,640
Let's go.

624
00:38:31,660 --> 00:38:35,260
(Starlight Camping Fair)

625
00:38:35,630 --> 00:38:37,000
You can give it a squeeze.

626
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:45,680
Tang,

627
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,070
I wanna get you something.

628
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:50,480
You've helped me so much.

629
00:38:50,630 --> 00:38:51,470
Here. It's for you.

630
00:38:54,550 --> 00:38:56,880
This doesn't count
as bribing a cop, right?

631
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:01,400
You said

632
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:02,920
you felt guilty.

633
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:04,630
Then you buy me a gift too.

634
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:06,070
We're even.

635
00:39:07,070 --> 00:39:08,670
Okay. Then…

636
00:39:09,670 --> 00:39:10,510
This is for you.

637
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:12,160
Thank you.

638
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:35,720
Li,

639
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:39,960
you said you're moving

640
00:39:41,150 --> 00:39:42,590
and quitting the dog shelter too.

641
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:46,510
That puts me in a tough spot.

642
00:39:49,630 --> 00:39:50,480
Mr. Bai,

643
00:39:52,030 --> 00:39:52,960
you know,

644
00:39:54,630 --> 00:39:56,110
in this world,

645
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:58,670
money's the only thing that's real.

646
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:00,590
I'm doing this

647
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:03,190
for our long-term plan.

648
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,440
If we keep playing small,

649
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,280
well,

650
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:10,030
when do we ever get big?

651
00:40:10,230 --> 00:40:11,070
Right?

652
00:40:11,230 --> 00:40:12,230
You know how hard

653
00:40:12,230 --> 00:40:13,590
I got hit last time.

654
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:16,150
If I don't fix this,

655
00:40:17,070 --> 00:40:18,670
my men out there

656
00:40:18,710 --> 00:40:20,030
are gonna go hungry.

657
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:23,280
Yeah.

658
00:40:24,440 --> 00:40:27,110
We've worked together a while.

659
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:29,000
You know what I'm capable of.

660
00:40:30,150 --> 00:40:31,480
Play it by ear.

661
00:40:32,590 --> 00:40:33,430
No problem.

662
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:36,280
But sometimes an opportunity

663
00:40:38,030 --> 00:40:39,550
can be a trap.

664
00:40:43,150 --> 00:40:44,550
Keep your eyes open.

665
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:49,440
The way you put it

666
00:40:50,030 --> 00:40:51,360
is interesting, Bai.

667
00:40:53,150 --> 00:40:54,960
You're my opportunity, aren't you?

668
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,630
Are you my trap?

669
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,880
I'm kidding.

670
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,840
Look, I've thought it through.

671
00:41:19,190 --> 00:41:20,760
Our old route

672
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:22,360
still works.

673
00:41:22,510 --> 00:41:24,230
But now there's a new model.

674
00:41:25,230 --> 00:41:27,000
You keep doing what you do.

675
00:41:27,150 --> 00:41:30,320
I'll give you a safer place to operate

676
00:41:31,070 --> 00:41:33,590
and solid cover.

677
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:35,550
It's a win-win. Why wouldn't we go for it?

678
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:42,400
Also,

679
00:41:45,030 --> 00:41:46,670
I know you and Wang Li

680
00:41:46,670 --> 00:41:48,230
don't get along.

681
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:49,680
Right?

682
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:53,800
I'm with you. Always.

683
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:56,760
I see.

684
00:41:57,590 --> 00:41:58,920
If you've got a plan,

685
00:41:59,230 --> 00:42:00,590
we'll do it your way.

686
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:02,920
That's the spirit.

687
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:04,670
We're partners after all,

688
00:42:04,670 --> 00:42:06,800
trust is everything, right?

689
00:42:11,190 --> 00:42:13,070
But speaking of that,

690
00:42:14,510 --> 00:42:16,320
about my last loss,

691
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:18,280
when can we settle that?

692
00:42:18,590 --> 00:42:19,510
You know last time,

693
00:42:19,510 --> 00:42:22,710
I pissed off some big shots.

694
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:24,000
Greasing palms

695
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:25,230
cost me a fortune.

696
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:26,880
That's not even the worst part.

697
00:42:28,670 --> 00:42:31,320
It makes everything harder going forward.

698
00:42:33,630 --> 00:42:34,470
Don't worry.

699
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,840
If I say I'll fix it, I'll fix it.

700
00:42:39,150 --> 00:42:40,400
And I'll even get you

701
00:42:42,030 --> 00:42:42,870
a surprise.

702
00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:46,880
Man,

703
00:42:47,030 --> 00:42:48,960
Bai, you've got real pull.

704
00:42:50,110 --> 00:42:52,480
I can't live without you.

705
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:56,230
By the way,

706
00:42:58,360 --> 00:43:00,110
about that overseas investment,

707
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:03,230
I wanna pause it.

708
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,070
Can you pull my money out?

709
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:07,760
I need it.

710
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:15,280
Sure.

711
00:43:55,440 --> 00:43:57,110
♪No holding back, no final hug♪

712
00:43:57,280 --> 00:43:59,070
♪No time to say goodbye♪

713
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:00,840
♪No trouble, no clinging on♪

714
00:44:01,030 --> 00:44:02,670
♪Keeping the last bit of pride♪

715
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:05,480
♪Not sure how far we walked hand in hand♪

716
00:44:05,550 --> 00:44:08,960
♪And now it circles back to the start♪

717
00:44:10,190 --> 00:44:11,880
♪No word from you, no contact♪

718
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:13,920
♪As if you were never here♪

719
00:44:14,540 --> 00:44:16,860
(Hongyun Restaurant)

720
00:44:28,740 --> 00:44:29,860
(Tang Tang)

721
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:33,320
♪So many regrets♪

722
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:37,000
♪So much unwillingness to let go♪

723
00:44:37,280 --> 00:44:40,480
♪Like a moon one night away from full♪

724
00:44:40,480 --> 00:44:42,030
Did you see the photos I sent?

725
00:44:42,360 --> 00:44:44,110
Li Xu's moving everything

726
00:44:44,110 --> 00:44:45,510
into Hongyun Restaurant.

727
00:44:45,670 --> 00:44:47,320
I'm hanging out with Wang Yimo.

728
00:44:47,630 --> 00:44:48,590
I asked her about it.

729
00:44:48,590 --> 00:44:50,360
She doesn't know the details, Master.

730
00:44:50,670 --> 00:44:51,510
She doesn't know?

731
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,510
Her dad runs the place.

732
00:44:53,510 --> 00:44:54,440
How would he not know?

733
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:55,840
Also,

734
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:58,280
I just saw the two dog thieves

735
00:44:58,360 --> 00:44:59,840
live-streaming on Shopping Street.

736
00:45:00,070 --> 00:45:01,070
You're near,

737
00:45:01,150 --> 00:45:02,280
so get over there quick.

738
00:45:02,480 --> 00:45:04,230
Watch Wang Yimo's reaction.

739
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:05,800
See if they

740
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:06,800
know each other.

741
00:45:07,630 --> 00:45:08,550
Listen.

742
00:45:08,920 --> 00:45:10,070
You're working a case.

743
00:45:10,670 --> 00:45:11,840
Use your head.

744
00:45:15,760 --> 00:45:16,600
Hey,

745
00:45:18,070 --> 00:45:19,590
you're shorting the weight.

746
00:45:19,880 --> 00:45:21,630
That's cheating.

747
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:22,960
Watch your mouth.

748
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:24,550
I'm a small business.

749
00:45:24,710 --> 00:45:25,800
Can't take your crap.

750
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:26,800
Cut it out. Move.

751
00:45:26,800 --> 00:45:28,400
Who's talking nonsense?

752
00:45:29,110 --> 00:45:30,360
I bought one kilo.

753
00:45:30,360 --> 00:45:31,480
You gave me this tiny bag.

754
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:32,360
How's that right?

755
00:45:33,070 --> 00:45:34,670
Bag size has nothing to do

756
00:45:34,670 --> 00:45:35,840
with weight.

757
00:45:36,510 --> 00:45:37,670
I'm not selling cotton.

758
00:45:37,670 --> 00:45:38,840
Pears are heavy.

759
00:45:38,840 --> 00:45:39,680
Heavy?

760
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:41,760
Did you just say they're heavy?

761
00:45:41,960 --> 00:45:42,960
So you admit

762
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:45,360
you pressed the scale, right?

763
00:45:45,760 --> 00:45:47,510
You're twisting my words.

764
00:45:47,630 --> 00:45:48,960
That's not what it means.

765
00:45:49,030 --> 00:45:51,070
Buy it or leave.

766
00:45:51,230 --> 00:45:52,760
What do you mean by that?

767
00:45:52,760 --> 00:45:53,620
(Dalong and Xiaohu)
What do you mean?

768
00:45:53,630 --> 00:45:54,960
Forced sales now?

769
00:45:56,510 --> 00:45:57,840
Everyone, look!

770
00:45:58,230 --> 00:46:00,230
I'm shopping

771
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:02,030
and I run into a shady vendor.

772
00:46:02,110 --> 00:46:03,070
(Dalong and Xiaohu)
Now he's getting physical

773
00:46:03,070 --> 00:46:04,000
and forcing sales.

774
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:04,840
Stop pushing me.

775
00:46:04,850 --> 00:46:06,030
It's consumer justice, okay?

776
00:46:06,230 --> 00:46:07,230
Look, everyone.

777
00:46:10,030 --> 00:46:11,280
Miss, come here.

778
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:12,440
Don't pull me.

779
00:46:12,900 --> 00:46:13,760
That's your boyfriend?

780
00:46:13,760 --> 00:46:14,710
You two look great.

781
00:46:15,150 --> 00:46:16,150
Help me judge this.

782
00:46:16,150 --> 00:46:17,480
Look.

783
00:46:17,590 --> 00:46:18,960
A sweet couple

784
00:46:18,960 --> 00:46:19,960
go out shopping

785
00:46:20,030 --> 00:46:22,110
and get tricked by vendors like you.

786
00:46:22,110 --> 00:46:23,230
They'll go home and fight.

787
00:46:23,400 --> 00:46:24,480
Fight, they break up.

788
00:46:24,550 --> 00:46:25,510
Break up, no marriage.

789
00:46:25,510 --> 00:46:26,920
No marriage, no kids.

790
00:46:26,920 --> 00:46:27,800
No kids

791
00:46:27,800 --> 00:46:29,070
doesn't fit the policy goals.

792
00:46:29,070 --> 00:46:31,030
You're basically against social progress.

793
00:46:32,070 --> 00:46:33,030
What proof do you have

794
00:46:33,030 --> 00:46:34,550
he's shorting weight?

795
00:46:34,590 --> 00:46:35,960
I've been watching.

796
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:37,800
You two are the ones causing trouble.

797
00:46:39,110 --> 00:46:40,000
I see.

798
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:42,190
Partners, huh?

799
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,360
Black-hearted, aren't you?

800
00:46:45,360 --> 00:46:47,550
You psycho. Move.

801
00:46:47,590 --> 00:46:48,550
That's ridiculous.

802
00:46:48,710 --> 00:46:50,360
Hands on me again, huh?

803
00:46:50,480 --> 00:46:51,630
Hit me again.

804
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:52,720
You think

805
00:46:53,070 --> 00:46:54,670
I'll let you...

806
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:09,880
(Police)
I didn't hit him.

807
00:47:09,920 --> 00:47:12,400
Officer, why are you arresting me?

808
00:47:12,710 --> 00:47:13,920
Everyone saw it.

809
00:47:13,920 --> 00:47:15,710
I didn't throw the first punch!

810
00:47:16,110 --> 00:47:17,710
- You have to be fair.
- I didn't do it.

811
00:47:17,710 --> 00:47:18,760
Everyone saw it.

812
00:47:20,760 --> 00:47:22,440
Tang, I saw it.

813
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:24,110
The vendor hit first.

814
00:47:25,400 --> 00:47:26,240
You okay?

815
00:47:26,440 --> 00:47:27,280
I'm fine.

816
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:29,150
I'm taking them in

817
00:47:29,150 --> 00:47:30,150
to ask something else.

818
00:47:30,190 --> 00:47:31,030
I'm going.

819
00:47:31,800 --> 00:47:32,920
- Okay.
- Bye.

820
00:47:33,030 --> 00:47:33,870
Bye.

821
00:47:50,030 --> 00:47:50,870
Drive.

822
00:47:51,460 --> 00:47:52,510
(Serve the People - Mao Zedong)

823
00:47:52,510 --> 00:47:54,710
Officer, we'll come clean.

824
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:58,440
Today was our fault.

825
00:47:58,590 --> 00:48:00,230
But it's for the data.

826
00:48:00,230 --> 00:48:02,000
We just wanted some hype.

827
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:03,760
Nothing more than that.

828
00:48:07,150 --> 00:48:08,230
You seem pretty pleased.

829
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:12,230
No, not at all.

830
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:14,280
Just answer what you're asked.

831
00:48:14,440 --> 00:48:15,960
Stop rambling so much.

832
00:48:17,760 --> 00:48:18,840
Dog theft and poisoned bait.

833
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:20,510
You've got the whole city freaked out.

834
00:48:21,070 --> 00:48:21,920
Talk.

835
00:48:22,340 --> 00:48:23,400
How much were you involved?

836
00:48:24,710 --> 00:48:25,800
Dogs…

837
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:27,760
Yeah,

838
00:48:27,960 --> 00:48:29,590
we did steal a few.

839
00:48:29,760 --> 00:48:30,600
But...

840
00:48:31,030 --> 00:48:32,550
But poisoning? No way.

841
00:48:32,550 --> 00:48:34,800
That anesthetic dose,

842
00:48:34,830 --> 00:48:35,950
it'd knock a small dog out

843
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:38,030
for like three to five minutes.

844
00:48:38,190 --> 00:48:40,280
We stole a few before.

845
00:48:40,590 --> 00:48:41,550
We're done now.

846
00:48:41,840 --> 00:48:43,280
We're doing new media now.

847
00:48:43,510 --> 00:48:45,320
Then where were you two

848
00:48:45,520 --> 00:48:46,630
from Sept 3rd to Sept 9th?

849
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:48,710
Sept 3rd…

850
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:50,880
I... I...

851
00:48:52,920 --> 00:48:54,440
I don't track dates.

852
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:55,510
I was with my brother.

853
00:48:55,510 --> 00:48:56,480
We're always together.

854
00:48:56,480 --> 00:48:59,000
We just wander.

855
00:48:59,110 --> 00:49:00,550
Anywhere.

856
00:49:00,670 --> 00:49:01,920
Did you go to Huacai Community?

857
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:03,480
What?

858
00:49:03,590 --> 00:49:05,070
Huacai Community.

859
00:49:05,230 --> 00:49:07,630
That area.

860
00:49:08,280 --> 00:49:10,280
Yeah, we went there.

861
00:49:10,550 --> 00:49:11,800
But officer, I swear,

862
00:49:11,800 --> 00:49:13,150
we were just walking around.

863
00:49:13,280 --> 00:49:15,000
Didn't do anything.

864
00:49:15,110 --> 00:49:16,710
You got someone above you?

865
00:49:16,960 --> 00:49:18,190
Someone directing you?

866
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:20,760
Zhang Ming?

867
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:22,760
He's like our big bro.

868
00:49:23,860 --> 00:49:25,070
We were gonna do something big,

869
00:49:25,070 --> 00:49:26,800
but his boss said no,

870
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:28,150
so he backed off.

871
00:49:28,360 --> 00:49:29,550
He's got a boss too?

872
00:49:29,710 --> 00:49:31,230
Yeah. Sometimes he asks us

873
00:49:31,230 --> 00:49:32,440
to snatch a dog or something.

874
00:49:32,440 --> 00:49:34,630
We always follow the orders.

875
00:49:34,760 --> 00:49:36,000
But we've never met him.

876
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:36,840
Never saw his face.

877
00:49:37,710 --> 00:49:39,400
This isn't a huge crime, right?

878
00:49:40,230 --> 00:49:41,960
Their movements match,

879
00:49:42,070 --> 00:49:43,960
but no purchase record or prints.

880
00:49:43,960 --> 00:49:45,880
Zhang Ming contacts them directly,

881
00:49:45,910 --> 00:49:46,800
but they say

882
00:49:46,800 --> 00:49:48,360
there's a boss above him.

883
00:49:48,360 --> 00:49:49,280
They're this loud.

884
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:50,630
Who's behind them?

885
00:49:50,920 --> 00:49:53,070
We've caught a lot of dog thieves lately.

886
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:55,070
These two are the closest fit.

887
00:49:57,960 --> 00:49:58,840
What's up, Master?

888
00:49:59,480 --> 00:50:00,480
These two punks…

889
00:50:01,400 --> 00:50:02,240
Look at this.

890
00:50:06,230 --> 00:50:07,480
This doesn't show a face.

891
00:50:07,510 --> 00:50:08,840
We can't confirm.

892
00:50:09,550 --> 00:50:11,320
It's him. No doubt.

893
00:50:15,310 --> 00:50:16,370
Get the whole team on this.

894
00:50:16,440 --> 00:50:17,440
Grab all shelter footage

895
00:50:17,480 --> 00:50:19,190
for that window and a two-day buffer.

896
00:50:19,230 --> 00:50:20,190
Cross-check it all.

897
00:50:20,440 --> 00:50:22,030
I want this guy found.

898
00:50:28,140 --> 00:50:33,630
♪Dreams of the past sleep in the chill♪

899
00:50:33,630 --> 00:50:37,080
♪Now I run toward the light♪

900
00:50:38,930 --> 00:50:44,190
♪What does the fire burn,
what does it reveal?♪

901
00:50:44,510 --> 00:50:48,160
♪Is the answer found when the sun rises♪

902
00:50:48,770 --> 00:50:53,060
♪If it's all a lie♪

903
00:50:54,250 --> 00:50:58,420
♪Should I tear it open?♪

904
00:50:59,750 --> 00:51:04,470
♪If it's all part of the journey♪

905
00:51:05,150 --> 00:51:10,000
♪Then face the blaze head-on♪

906
00:51:10,390 --> 00:51:14,860
♪Let the sun awaken my heart's crave♪

907
00:51:15,400 --> 00:51:21,130
♪Pain reminds me I'm alive♪

908
00:51:21,250 --> 00:51:26,060
♪The world can't take away every clear sky♪

909
00:51:26,710 --> 00:51:31,860
♪The hotter it gets, the fiercer I fight♪

910
00:51:32,170 --> 00:51:36,890
♪Let the sun burn away all I lean upon♪

911
00:51:37,230 --> 00:51:42,890
♪Leave me only what endures♪

912
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:48,550
♪At the cliff's edge, all fear shatters♪

913
00:51:48,610 --> 00:51:55,560
♪With a grounded heart, a soul like fire♪
